      "forkOfPackageId": "datarex:RDM-MM:0.1.1",
      "id": "datarex:RDM-MM:0.1.2",
      "kmId": "RDM-MM",
      "license": "ELIXIR",
      "mergeCheckpointPackageId": "datarex:RDM-MM:0.1.1",
      "metamodelVersion": 20,
      "name": "Maturity Model of Research Data Management ",
      "nonEditable": false,
      "organizationId": "datarex",
      "phase": "ReleasedKnowledgeModelPackagePhase",
      "previousPackageId": "datarex:RDM-MM:0.1.1",
      "readme": "# Maturity Model of Research Data Management \nThis is a DSW representation of Research Data Management (RDM) Maturity Model. The Maturity Model is a structured framework that helps institutes assess and systematically improve their RDM services by defining progressive levels of capability across key areas. The model enables instituts to evaluate their status across 27 indicators in four domains: strategy, legal, training, and data.\n\nCurrent version of the Maturity Model contains only a list of indicators (with description) and maturity levels. Future development will add links and guidelines on how to progress between levels.\n\n## Acknowledgement:\nRDM Maturity Model is [ELIXIR RDM community](https://elixir-europe.org/communities/research-data-management) driven project. \n\nThis work was supported by ELIXIR, the research infrastructure for life science data. In particular through ELIXIR Implementation Study [DATAREX](https://elixir-europe.org/internal-projects/commissioned-services/datarex) (Data Management for Research in ELIXIR).\n\n**Authors in alphabetical order:**\n- Minna Ahokas\n- Federico Bianchini\n- Korbinian Bösl\n- Alessandro Cestaro\n- Flora D'Anna\n- Vilém Děd\n- Nazeefa Fatima\n- Niclas Jareborg\n- Mijke Jetten\n- Luka Kranjc\n- Brane Leskošek\n- Flavio Licciulli\n- Aída Moure Fernández\n- Ivan Mičetić\n- Minna Ahokas\n- Anna Niehues\n- Xenia Perez Sitja\n- Diana Pilvar\n- Gil Poiares-Oliveira\n- Marina Popleteeva\n- Amir Szitenberg\n- Jeanne Wilbrandt\n\n## Changelog:\n- 0.1.2 Prepared for publishing in DSW Registry\n- 0.1.1 Initial version created as part of [DATAREX](https://elixir-europe.org/internal-projects/commissioned-services/datarex) event in Bari 24-26 March 2025.\n\n",
      "version": "0.1.2"
    }
  ],
  "version": "0.1.2"
}
